   13016             : accessed from a friend or member function of a derived class be
   13017             : accessed through an object of the derived class or a class further
   13018             : derived from that.  sym is the member (not overloaded, possibly a
   13019             : projection symbol).  proj_sym is the same as sym, or is the overloaded
   13020             : function symbol that contains sym, or it can be a projection symbol
   13021             : for either of those.  The class of proj_sym is the "naming class" of
   13022             : the reference, as defined by the standard.  access_class is the class
   13023             : of the pointer or object through which the member is being accessed.
   13024             : access_class is NULL if we don't know the object type (which will
   13025             : cause an error).  access_class may also be an error type (which will
   13026             : cause no error).  *err_pos is the source position for an error; if
   13027             : it is NULL, no error is put out.  In all cases, the result value is
   13028             : TRUE if the access is okay, and FALSE if there is an error.  This
   13029             : routine is called only for nonstatic members, but it has not yet been
   13030             : established that the member is protected in the naming class.
   13031             : If error_detected is non-NULL, return *error_detected set to TRUE if
